President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring October 2019 as National Energy Awareness Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the revitalization of the country's energy sector, with increased crude oil production, becoming a net exporter of natural gas, and increased coal exports. The administration aims to continue promoting responsible stewardship of the environment while fully utilizing America's energy resources. The Department of Energy is operating test facilities to develop emissions-free nuclear reactor technology, and collaboration with industry and academia is encouraged for the research and development of advanced energy technologies. The proclamation also emphasizes the importance of maintaining a modern and secure network of energy infrastructure and supporting the energy workforce. Overall, the proclamation aims to ensure a more secure and prosperous future for all Americans through advancements in the energy sector.